  "title": "Equipment Technician (3 years contract/ PVD/ Etch/ CVD)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>First line troubleshooting for equipment related issues</li><li>Execute scheduled and unscheduled equipment maintenance and Post PM process recovery</li><li>Responsible for equipment uptimeand liaison with process control team and equipment vendors for resolving escalations and SPC deviation.</li><li>Works with process module development team, process control team and vendor to ensure flawless operations.</li><li>Support internal audits as needed for ISO certification.</li><li>Able to work under shift independently.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Electrical and Electronics, Mechanical, Mechatronics Engineering</li><li>Preferably with minimum 2 years of semiconductor equipment engineering experience (in the domain of Etch, PVD, PECVD) with hands-on equipment troubleshooting experience</li><li>Systematic and logical thinking.</li><li>Candidate must be comfortable to communicate with inter-department at any technical level</li><li></li></ul><p>To find out more about this opportunity, please contact <strong>Lionel Liew </strong>at\n<strong>lionel.liew@gmprecruit.com</strong>.</p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd  |   EA Licence: 11C3793|   EA Personnel: Lionel Liew   |  \nRegistration No: R1330693</p><p><em>This is in partnership with the Employment and Employability Institute Pte Ltd (“e2i”).</em></p><p><em>e2i is the empowering network for workers and\nemployers seeking employment and employability solutions. e2i serves as a\nbridge between workers and employers, connecting with workers to offer job\nsecurity through job-matching, career guidance and skills upgrading services,\nand partnering employers to address their manpower needs through recruitment,\ntraining, and job redesign solutions. e2i is a tripartite initiative of the\nNational Trades Union Congress set up to support nation-wide manpower and\nskills upgrading initiatives.</em></p><p><em>By applying for this role, you consent to GMP\nTechnologies (S) Pte Ltd’s </em><a href=\"https://www.gmprecruit.com/legal/privacy-policy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>PDPA</em></a><em> and </em><a href=\"https://us-west-2.protection.sophos.com?d=e2i.com.sg&u=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZTJpLmNvbS5zZy9wZHBhLw==&i=NThlNDdhOGMyYmI5N2YwZmQxZDk4NjQw&t=cWdqRFV0Uy80RjN3MDlSYmM1dS85VTRxVTRoYVlXdWFyWTYzaGlVS3k0TT0=&h=1ad0460f503340658fbeab159c31256f&s=AVNPUEhUT0NFTkNSWVBUSVaVGQEVMuPAipiPENS4aadnRg3RqoiWpHBKgNtumWhHjA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>e2i’s PDPA</em></a><em>.</em></p>",
